<TITLE> Aziz to join 3-day Doha talks on global crisis </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam will join a three-day ministerial level meeting on the global economic crisis in the Qatar capital of Doha scheduled to open on Saturday, ministry officials said on Thursday. The finance adviser told bdnews24.com: "The meeting is vitally important for south Asia and the Middle East specially for Bangladesh as it will discuss ways to avert the impacts of the global financial quandary." Finance ministers from South Asia including Bangladesh, India and Pakistan and the Middle East will attend the meeting. Representatives from the World Bank, Asian Development Bank, International Monetary Fund and developed nations will also join the meeting. The finance adviser will leave for Doha on Saturday and will return on Dec 2, officials said. bdnews
